nd from the pre-Christian ancient world, yet have nothing Christian about them. It was in fact nineteenth-century scholars who attempted to establish the narrative of pagan survival that persists today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aGoddessesxHistoriography. 0aGoddessesxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / Middle Ages (449-1066).2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311074977940uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300265279?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300265279423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300265279/original  a978-3-11-074977-9  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles